Written as {{och-l|建|tr=*kar}} in the Haihunhou bamboo slips, {{och-l|鍵|tr=*garʔ}} in the Mawangdui silk texts, {{zh-l|*天目}} in the Wangjiatai Qin bamboo slips, and {{och-l|倝}} in the Tsinghua bamboo slips.

{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2014: p. 274)}} proposes that {{och-l|乾|tr= {{IPAfont|*gran}}}} (> {{w|Qieyun|QYS}} {{IPAfont|*gjän}}) "looks like the same etymon as" {{och-l|祁連|tr= {{IPAfont|*gɨ-lian}}}}, ancient pronunciation of {{w|Qilian Mountains}}' name.

